I’m so proud of the work the FTC did to bring Invitation Homes to account for their greedy practices, resulting in a $48 million settlement for affected renters.

Invitation Homes also systematically withheld renters’ security deposits, including by unfairly charging them for normal wear-and-tear, damages that existed before renters moved in, & even renovations.

Invitation Homes’ marketing materials claim that every home the company rents passes a “quality assurance inspection” & that the company provides “24/7 emergency maintenance.”

But there are numerous instances of new renters arriving at a home to find it in significant disrepair.

According to the complaint, Invitation Homes advertised monthly rental rates that didn’t include mandatory junk fees that could add more than $1,700 yearly.

Consumers looking for rentals paid nonrefundable fees—including application fees up to $55 & reservation fees up to $500.

Every person deserves a safe and secure home, period.
